social_posts.post_text: Life has been crazy busy with the holidays & birthdays because THIS LITTLE MAN TURNED SIX YEARS OLD THE DAY BEFORE THANKSGIVING 😭😍🥳 Jack, you are such a blessing to all who know you. You love the Lord and always stop to pray or sing or talk about God, which just warms this mamas heart SO much. You have the sweetest, kindest, most loving and empathetic heart and your smile just lights up a room. You are incredibly smart and it always amazes me how much you excel at learning (seriously he works so hard and is already going up a grade in school). You are so gracious & give to everyone you know (even if it’s hardest to give to your little sis sometimes 😜). You’re an all in kind of guy and I am so proud of the little gentleman you’re turning into. It feels like just yesterday you were my little baby squishy boy and I love every moment of watching you grow. My cuddle bug, my little best friend who will talk to me for hours about life and everything in between. We spent his special day doing all of Jack’s favorite things & it was so much fun to just celebrate YOU! I’m so proud of you, Jack. I love you forever and always 💛

Only 7 more days until Christmas and there’s no better way to celebrate than worshipping Jesus!!! 😍🎄 His Glory Music Christmas Special is live TODAY at 11am pst / 2pm est on their @hisglorymusic_ YouTube channel & over on @hisgloryme ❤️💚 We were able to visit the set and my goodness, it was just filled with the Holy Spirit 🔥 We laughed, we cried, we celebrated the birth of our Savior 🥰 I also just have to shout out to this amazing team…I’ve never seen a group bring God into every moment and it’s so humbling to watch them all just let loose, play, and give the music to Him. It’s been a beautiful experience being able to watch them all work and then in turn, watching the Lord work through them 🥰 Adore all of you so much!

Merry Christmas & Happy Holidays to everyone ❤️ All glory to the newborn King 😍 Praising and thanking God for sending His son, Jesus, as a savior to ALL! And so incredibly grateful for family, love, joy, and peace in this holiday season. Sending you all so much love from me and my favorite tribe of goofballs (swipe to see us being silly 😜). I love always laughing through life with these three, God is so good 🥰

One of my hopes for the New Year was to be better at posting…it’s 3 days into 2023 and I completely forgot to post this 😂🤣 ANYWAYS, I may not be the best at posting these days…but I wish you all the happiest New Year ✨ I feel so incredibly blessed for all of the happiness, joy, changes, love, and smiles that 2022 brought us. Here’s to all the beautiful things God has in store for 2023 🥳

Happy 4th birthday to the living embodiment of sugar, spice, & everything nice ✨ Adaline, my beautiful little girl…I am so incredibly blessed to be your mama. You live every moment full send, no brakes, no halves, just unapologetically in whatever moment you’re in. You are fierce and protective of those you love…and yet you have the sweetest empathy for everyone you meet. You never miss an opportunity to stop and pray for someone & ask God for all of your big dreams. My little Dramadaline, you’re a natural born performer, always singing or acting around the house. The silliest little pint sized Princess who loves a good fart joke. Full Princess, Full Superhero…You’re an oxymoron, just like your mama 😉💛 I love you more than simple words and I am so incredibly proud of who you are at the young age of 4 😍 We spent a day at Disney to celebrate Miss Addie’s birthday last week and it was the best day ever. Today, we get to shower you with even more love, hugs, and fun! I love you my little best friend 🥰 …now excuse me while I go cry a river because my youngest baby is 4 years old 😭
